1 Loading packages

requiredPackages = c('tidyverse', 'reshape2', 'knitr', 'cowplot', 'Hmisc', 'corrplot', 'zoo')

for(p in requiredPackages){
  if(!require(p,character.only = TRUE)) install.packages(p)
  library(p,character.only = TRUE)
}

2 Reading the data

dat1 <- read_csv("pros.csv") %>% 
  dplyr::select(-Group) %>% 
  mutate(speaker = factor(speaker),
         GroupFull = factor(GroupFull),
         Gender = factor(Gender),
         Lang = factor(Lang))
dat2 <- read_csv("vq.csv") %>% 
  dplyr::select(-Group) %>% 
  mutate(speaker = factor(speaker),
         GroupFull = factor(GroupFull),
         Gender = factor(Gender),
         Lang = factor(Lang))
dat3 <- read_csv("neuropsych.csv") %>% 
  dplyr::select(-Group) %>% 
  mutate(speaker = factor(speaker),
         GroupFull = factor(GroupFull),
         Gender = factor(Gender),
         Lang = factor(Lang))

3 Summaries and visualisations

3.1 Prosody

3.1.1 Manipulations

We read in the data and change it to a dataframe and change some variables into factors.

dat1SC <- dat1 %>% 
  dplyr::select(-c(ed_yrs, NrofNuclei, PropPhon, F0MedianHz, F0MeanHz, F0StdevHz, PitchTopHz, PitchBottomHz, RawF0_p02, RawF0_p98, RawF0_mean)) %>%
  mutate(Gender = ifelse(Gender == "Female", 1, -1),
         Lang = ifelse(Lang == "spa", 1, -1),
         GroupFull = factor(GroupFull, levels = c("HC", "SCD", "naMCI", "aMCI", "pAD"))) %>% 
  group_by(GroupFull) %>%
  mutate_all(na.aggregate, FUN = mean)
dat1SC <- as.data.frame(dat1SC)

dat1SC
write.csv(dat1SC, "prosodySC.csv")

3.1.2 Plots variables

box_fun_plot = function(data, x, y) {
  ggplot(data = data, aes(x = .data[[x]],
                          y = .data[[y]],
                          fill = .data[[x]])) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    labs(title = y,
         x = x,
         y = y) +
    theme(
      legend.position = "none"
    ) +
    theme_bw()
}

# Create vector of predictors
expl <- names(dat1SC)[-(dim(dat1SC)[2])]

# Loop vector with map
expl_plots_box <- map(expl, ~box_fun_plot(data = dat1SC, x = "GroupFull", y = .x) )
plot_grid(plotlist = expl_plots_box)

3.1.3 Summaries of data

dat1SC %>% 
  group_by(GroupFull) %>% 
  dplyr::select(where(is.numeric)) %>% 
  summarise_all(funs(mean = mean, sd = sd, var = var, min = min, max = max, median = median, Q1 = quantile(., probs = 0.25), Q3 = quantile(., probs = 0.75)), na.rm = TRUE)
